@node Intro   "Introduction"
@next Install
@toc  Main
WBStartup++ 1.47                                               25-Nov-2000





     I've used the original WBStartup+ written by John Hughes for a long
     time  but since the introduction of the new icon format with OS 3.5
     the little startup window of WBStartup+ looked very ugly.

     So  I've  decided  to write my own and add some nice features.  You
     can  still  use  the  old preferences program.
     
     Requirements: 

       Computer : An Amiga, what else :)
       OS       : 3.5 +
       Library  : wbstart.library version 2.2 (no higher version) 
     
@endnode

@node Install "Installation"
@next Use
@toc  Main
WBStartup++ 1.47                                               25-Nov-2000





     The  installation  is  very simple.  I think, that I don't need the
     Installer for this files.  The WBStartup++ program should be copied
     to  the  WBStartup  directory  where  it should be the only program
     beside the "enabled" and "disabled" drawer.
     
     To  change the look of WBStartup++ you can set different tooltypes.
     Only a few of them are fully compatible to the old version.

     @{b}Tooltypes@{ub} -------------------------------------------------------

     ENABLEDPATH   = path       Directory for all the programs wich
                                should be started

     DISABLEDPATH  = path       Directory for all disabled programs

     PREFSPATH     = path       Path to the preferences program

     BACKGROUND    = path       Path to the background picture

     TRANSPARENT                Uses the wb background as window pattern

     BORDERLESS                 Draws the window without a border

     POSITION      = x,y        Window position
              or
     POSITION      = CENTER     Window will be centered on the screen

     MACSTYLE      = width      Mac style startup display

     TEXTPEN       = n          Text color pen number 

     TOOLPRI       = n          Priority of WBStartUp++ 

     DELAY         = n          Start delay in 1/50 sec

@endnode

@node Use "Usage"
@next History
@toc  Main
WBStartup++ 1.47                                               25-Nov-2000





     Nothing  much  to say here. Just watch how the programs start :) If
     the  program  window opens you can press the "D" key to disable all
     programs or you can use "I" to switch to the interactive mode where
     you must confirm every program start.

     Keys: I - Interactive Mode
           D - Disable all

@endnode

